Design Patterns

	Usage of Design pattern

		Design patterns have two main usages in software development

		Common platform for developers:

			Provides a standard terminology and are specific to particular scenarios

				Singletons should follow a design pattern so that all developers familiar with singletons should be able to recognize and understand what is happening in the code

		Best Practices

			Patterns have been evolving over a long time and SHOULD provide the best solutions to certain problems faced during software development. These patterns help people with less experience design their software easier and more efficiently 